Package de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.injectors

Injectors for mRUBiS.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Abstract_PI_Injector
    Abstract class for injectors of performance issues.
    AbstractCF2_Injector
    Abstract injector for injecting a CF2 either by injecting more Exceptions than the given threshold (in this case, it is actually a CF2) or by injecting less Exceptions than the given threshold (in this case, exceptions occur but they do not cause a CF2).
    CF1_Injector
    Injects a CF1, that is, it sets the state of the given Component (see Component.getState() to ComponentState.UNKNOWN if the component is currently in state ComponentState.STARTED.
    CF2_Injector
    Injects a CF2, that is, it creates and adds Exceptions to the given ProvidedInterface if the component providing the interface is started and if at least one started component is using the provided interface.
    CF3_Injector
    Injects a CF3, that is, it completely removes a ComponentState.STARTED Component from the model including its contained elements, which are the Parameters, ProvidedInterfaces, and RequiredInterfaces with the associated Connectors.
    CF5_Injector
    Injects a CF5, that is, it removes a Connector between two ComponentState.STARTED Components.
    NoCF2_Injector
    Does not inject a CF2 but it creates and adds Exceptions to the given ProvidedInterface if the component providing the interface is started (see ComponentState.STARTED) and if at least one started component is using the provided interface.
    PI1_Injector
    Injects a PI1 by changing the selection rate and/or the local computation time of a filter Component so that the filter component is not located any more at its optimal position in the pipe of filters.
    PI2_Injector
    Injects a PI2 by changing the PerformanceStats of the personalized search within the given Tenant so that the average response time of the search is above the given threshold.
    PI3_Injector
    Injects a PI3 by changing the PerformanceStats of the personalized search within the given Tenant so that the average response time of the search is below the given threshold.
